The First Lady and President Trump send their warm wishes to those celebrating Diwali. Diwali is a Festival of Lights where people come together to celebrate the triumph of good over evil, light over darkness, and knowledge over ignorance. Lighting diyas symbolizes hope and devotion that faith and tradition bring. The United States is a nation that values religious freedom, and the President is proud of his Administration's work in defending the constitutional right of Americans to live and worship according to their conscience. The President hopes that wherever Diwali is celebrated, the United States serves as a beacon of religious liberty. This year, it is important to cherish and be grateful for the companionship of friends and family. The First Lady and President Trump wish everyone celebrating Diwali a joyous celebration and prosperous new beginnings.